    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-06-07</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-07-16T19:16:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Early Childhood Investment Act of 2007 - Authorizes the Secretary of Health and Human Services to award a three-to-five-year grant to not more than one public-private partnership in each state to promote school readiness by improving the quality of, and access to, early childhood development opportunities for children throughout the state from birth to kindergarten. </p> <p>Requires each partnership to include the state and at least one tax-exempt organization and be led by a board of directors.</p> <p>Reduces the federal share of the cost of activities assisted under this Act from 50% in the first year of a grant to 30% in the third and any succeeding year of the grant.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
